		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Likewise, on NT2, try setting an instrument's arpeggio X/Y/Z to C/C/C, 0/C/C, or 0/0/C, and turning <strong>ON!</strong> the last two unlabeled instrument settings (Arpeggio down and Arpeggio non-looping)
<br />
<br /><em>(checks his own NSFs for non-looped descending arpeggios)</em>
<br />dy-covers.nsf track 8, at 0:38, channels 1 and 2
<br />dy-covers.nsf track 11, at 0:46, channel 3
<br />dy-covers.nsf track 15, throughout, channels 1 and 2
<br />Opentris.nsf track 1, various points, channel 2
<br />Opentris.nsf track 3, at 1:20, channel 2
<br />Opentris.nsf track 9, various points, channels 2 and 3
<br />Opentris.nsf track 11, throughout, channel 3

		

